    "narrative": "The cornerstone of today's lineup is **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who commands the slate with a massive 86.99 efficiency score. His matchup against Lopez is optimal, buoyed by a significant park factor (+10%) and superior SP skill dynamics, making him our primary engine for counting stats. **Lawrence Butler** also earns a high-ceiling designation (70.08) despite hitting in the eight-hole; his 13% platoon edge and favorable park environment make him the best \"value-to-efficiency\" play on the board. Meanwhile, **Geraldo Perdomo** and **Taylor Ward** are providing excellent stability, with **Geraldo Perdomo** capitalizing on the park factors against Imanaga and **Taylor Ward** benefiting from a premium lead-off spot against a favorable SP skill profile.\n\nThe most difficult exclusion today was **Yainer Diaz**, who pushed for a spot with a 49.77 rating but ultimately fell victim to Early\u2019s elite 2.97 xERA. While the wind-out conditions and platoon advantage were enticing, the optimizer favored the higher scoring-floor of **Cal Raleigh** and **Will Smith** in their respective matchups against softer starters. We are monitoring **Wenceel Perez** and **Jeremiah Jackson** closely; while both possess valuable sprint speed, their sub-50 scores leave little margin for error, and they are essentially \"hold\" starts specifically to chase stolen bases in the late-innings against Rocker. \n\nWe must remain wary of the volatility surrounding **Gleyber Torres** and **Jonathan Aranda**. **Gleyber Torres** struggles with a negative platoon adjustment (-13%), and **Jonathan Aranda** is being deployed primarily as a high-floor filler at 1B. We are banking on the high-probability spots in the order for **Will Smith** and **Cal Raleigh** to provide the necessary cushion to keep our daily efficiency target intact. With no major weather delays forecasted, the primary risk remains the high SP skill of the opposing arms, particularly in the later games, so we will be evaluating pinch-hit opportunities if our depth pieces underperform early.",
